<DocsLayout title="Getting Started" description="Installation, project structure, and quick start guide">
	<section>
		<h2>Installation</h2>
		<p>You can <strong>install the npm package</strong> or <strong>run the CLI</strong>; both support npm, pnpm, yarn, and bun. Use the tabs below: click a tab to select your package manager, then copy the command. For the CLI: choose <strong>framework</strong> (Vanilla, Astro, or Svelte), then <strong>add to existing</strong> or <strong>create new project</strong>. <strong>Add to existing</strong> (or <code>npx rizzo-css add</code>): drop in CSS + hand-pick components; you must add the <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> yourself (CLI prints the exact tag). <strong>Create new</strong>: choose <strong>Full</strong> (everything), <strong>Minimal</strong> (recommended), or <strong>Manual</strong> (minimal base + component picker with minimal set pre-selected), then your package manager (npm, pnpm, yarn, bun). The package includes <code>dist/rizzo.min.css</code>, the CLI (<code>init</code> / <code>add</code> / <code>theme</code>), and scaffolds plus 25 optional components (including ThemeSwitcher). Scaffolds add <strong>README-RIZZO.md</strong> and <strong>LICENSE-RIZZO</strong> (do not overwrite your project README/LICENSE). Optional <strong>rizzo-css.json</strong> and flags: <code>init --yes --framework</code>, <code>--template</code>, <code>--install</code>, <code>--no-install</code>; <code>add --install-package</code>. See the <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/rizzo-css">npm package</a> and project README for CLI details.</p>

		<h3 class="docs-cli-heading">Install the npm package</h3>
		<p class="docs-cli-intro">Choose your package manager, then copy the command to add Rizzo CSS to your project.</p>
		<PackageInstallTabs class="docs-cli-tabs" />

		<h3 class="docs-cli-heading">Run the CLI</h3>
		<p class="docs-cli-intro">Click a tab to select your package manager, then use the copy button to copy the command.</p>
		<CliCommandTabs command="init" class="docs-cli-tabs" />
		<p class="docs-cli-label"><strong>Add to existing project:</strong></p>
		<CliCommandTabs command="add" class="docs-cli-tabs" />
		<p class="docs-cli-note">To add a specific component without prompts, include its name: e.g. <code>npx rizzo-css add Button</code> or <code>npx rizzo-css add ThemeSwitcher</code>. Some components add others automatically (e.g. Settings adds ThemeSwitcher; Toast adds Alert). Run <code>npx rizzo-css help components</code> for the full list. Each component doc page has the exact command with copy buttons. For <code>theme</code> (list theme IDs), use the same pattern: <code>npx rizzo-css theme</code>, <code>pnpm dlx rizzo-css theme</code>, and so on.</p>

		<p>Rizzo CSS is built on Astro. To work on this docs site and reference components (clone the repo):</p>
		<CodeBlock code={`# Clone the project
git clone <repository-url>
cd rizzo-css`} language="bash" />
		<CodeBlock code={`# Install dependencies
pnpm install`} language="nodejs" />
	</section>

